  "content": "\u003cp\u003eHello Mastodon,\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eI\u0026#39;m Kevin. I am a software engineer who likes to play with different network protocols to learn them.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eI\u0026#39;ve made an interactive map of the physical infrastructure of the global internet with undersea cables and peering data: \u003ca href=\"https://kmcd.dev/posts/internet-map-2025/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" translate=\"no\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"invisible\"\u003ehttps://\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"ellipsis\"\u003ekmcd.dev/posts/internet-map-20\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"invisible\"\u003e25/\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eI\u0026#39;ve made a series of posts trashing and praising the protocol I love to use to build cool things, gRPC: \u003ca href=\"https://kmcd.dev/posts/grpc-the-bad-parts/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" translate=\"no\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"invisible\"\u003ehttps://\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"ellipsis\"\u003ekmcd.dev/posts/grpc-the-bad-pa\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"invisible\"\u003erts/\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eI actually like gRPC so much that I did a whole series detailing how you can build your own gRPC server and client from scratch: \u003ca href=\"https://kmcd.dev/posts/grpc-from-scratch/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" translate=\"no\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"invisible\"\u003ehttps://\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"ellipsis\"\u003ekmcd.dev/posts/grpc-from-scrat\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"invisible\"\u003ech/\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eI\u0026#39;ve gotten thousands of people to whistle into their phones and computers to pretend to hack an old-school phone control system: \u003ca href=\"https://kmcd.dev/posts/can-you-hack-a-phone-with-your-voice/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" translate=\"no\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"invisible\"\u003ehttps://\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"ellipsis\"\u003ekmcd.dev/posts/can-you-hack-a-\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"invisible\"\u003ephone-with-your-voice/\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eI made a \u0026quot;typing\u0026quot; game, but with Morse code: \u003ca href=\"https://kmcd.dev/posts/morse/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" translate=\"no\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"invisible\"\u003ehttps://\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"\"\u003ekmcd.dev/posts/morse/\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"invisible\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e...and a lot more. Hopefully this gives you a glimpse into what I do on my free time!\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eMy latest post is about using code to generate artwork for my tech blog: \u003ca href=\"https://kmcd.dev/posts/cover-art/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" translate=\"no\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"invisible\"\u003ehttps://\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"\"\u003ekmcd.dev/posts/cover-art/\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"invisible\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eIf you like any of this stuff, toss me a follow or subscribe to the RSS feed.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThis was a really great year for me, but I intend to increase the frequency that I write posts going into the new year. I already have 3 more posts completed and scheduled to automatically publish, so stay tuned!\u003c/p\u003e",
